Reviews.Title: Great for the price, with some limitations
Reviews.Author: rad
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop after spending over 1k each of the last two years in a Samsung and an HP laptop, both of which died just past their first birthday. Tired of expensive and mediocre products I decided to purchase a 'cheap' laptop that stays at home and is used for browsing, watching movies, writing, and the occasional game. Mostly I play Paradox games, so my needs on the processor/graphics area are not that intensive (Playstation for that!). I think it is powerful enough most users; it manages multiple apps well and unless you're doing database stuff or gaming it should be just fine. Contrary to some reviews here I take no issue with the keyboard, although I guess that is somewhat personal; I do appreciate the Numpad. It is a large piece of equipment, which on one hand gives you a lot of screen real estate, but it is heavier than other laptops. The one complaint I have is that it has terrible speakers. To put it in perspective, an Ipad sounds better. So, if you want a laptop for 'home' use that is not expensive this is a great choice... just plan on buying additional speakers.

Reviews.Title: Very pleased.
Reviews.Author: Kanter "KO"
Reviews.Content: I am very pleased with this laptop (with Windows 7).  Several weeks ago I bought a HP Envy laptop (with Windows 8) via Amazon.  In the first week the HP laptop "froze" so many times that in the end I couldn't even log-in.  After going on-line to try and find a solution/cause for the constant freezing, I finally gave up after a week, packaged it up, and ordered this one.  Best move I ever made!I have had 2 previous Gateway laptops that had lasted over 5 years each (with heavy use).  This one was just as easy to get up and running as the previous ones were.  Their set-up instructions were very clear and helpful.The battery life of "up to 4.5 hrs" is very accurate.  I basically have never gotten under 4 hours. I've gotten over 4.5 hrs several times.  It's very consistent.  I had read on Gateway's web-site that it was recommended that the first three times you use your new laptop that you let the battery drain all the down and then charge it to full.  I did as recommended and it seems to have enabled a quicker charge to full (usually from totally drained to full in 1.5 hrs to 2.O hrs.)You cannot go wrong with this computer, especially at the price.
